"script": "A fighter pilot pulls the handle, and four seconds later he's floating safely under a parachute. But ejecting at 600 miles an hour should snap his spine. So how does he survive? First, explosive bolts blast the canopy clear of his head. Then a rocket motor fires under the seat, shoving him out with a force strong enough to crack ribs, but spread across his whole back. Next, a small chute yanks him free of the seat. And the main canopy opens before he even realizes he's left the plane behind.",
